00:21:24,712 --> 00:21:26,881
Suppose she'll
still be with him?

266
00:21:27,048 --> 00:21:28,382
Possibly, but...

267
00:21:28,382 --> 00:21:31,051
Marion's the least
of your worries right now,

268
00:21:31,051 --> 00:21:32,761
believe me, Indy.

269
00:21:32,803 --> 00:21:34,846
What do you mean?

270
00:21:34,846 --> 00:21:37,933
Well, I mean that
for nearly 3,000 years,

271
00:21:38,058 --> 00:21:40,852
man has been searching
for the Lost Ark.

272
00:21:40,852 --> 00:21:45,648
Not something to be taken
lightly.

273
00:21:45,773 --> 00:21:49,693
No one knows its secrets.

274
00:21:49,819 --> 00:21:53,197
It's like nothing you've ever
gone after before.

275
00:21:54,531 --> 00:21:55,699
Oh, Marcus.

276
00:21:55,699 --> 00:21:56,908
What are you trying to do,
scare me?

277
00:21:56,908 --> 00:21:57,868
You sound like my mother.

278
00:21:57,951 --> 00:21:59,411
We've known each other
for a long time.

279
00:21:59,411 --> 00:22:00,370
I don't believe in magic,

280
00:22:00,495 --> 00:22:02,539
a lot of superstitious
hocus-pocus.

281
00:22:02,705 --> 00:22:03,748
I'm going after a find

282
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:05,708
of incredible
historical significance.

283
00:22:05,792 --> 00:22:07,501
You're talking
about the bogeyman.

284
00:22:07,668 --> 00:22:10,838
Besides, you know
what a cautious fellow I am.

285
00:22:21,556 --> 00:22:22,807
Nice to see you again,
Dr. Jones.

286
00:22:22,849 --> 00:22:23,808
Thank you.

287
00:23:37,459 --> 00:23:38,793
Shh... shh...

288
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:58,728
Shh...

289
00:24:29,465 --> 00:24:31,467
Give him space!
Give him space!

290
00:24:31,508 --> 00:24:32,926
Go on, Regan!

291
00:24:34,678 --> 00:24:37,055
Shh! Shh!

292
00:24:37,055 --> 00:24:38,557
Shh! Shh! Shh!

293
00:25:23,389 --> 00:25:25,641
Hello, Marion.

294
00:25:31,272 --> 00:25:34,441
Indiana Jones.

295
00:25:36,526 --> 00:25:37,944
Always knew, someday,

296
00:25:38,111 --> 00:25:40,488
you'd come walking back
through my door.

297
00:25:40,488 --> 00:25:42,532
I never doubted that.

298
00:25:42,699 --> 00:25:44,951
Something made it inevitable.

299
00:25:44,951 --> 00:25:47,870
So, what are you doing here
in Nepal?

300
00:25:47,953 --> 00:25:50,873
I need one of the pieces
your father collected.

301
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:53,792
I learned to hate you
in the last ten years.

302
00:25:54,876 --> 00:25:56,545
I never meant to hurt you.

303
00:25:56,628 --> 00:25:57,796
I was a child.

304
00:25:57,879 --> 00:25:59,047
I was in love.

305
00:25:59,089 --> 00:26:00,882
It was wrong and you knew it!

306
00:26:01,049 --> 00:26:02,258
You knew what you were doing.

307
00:26:02,342 --> 00:26:02,842
Now I do!

308
00:26:03,009 --> 00:26:04,010
This is my place.

309
00:26:04,135 --> 00:26:05,219
Get out!

310
00:26:08,305 --> 00:26:09,265
I did what I did.

311
00:26:09,348 --> 00:26:10,724
You don't have to be happy
about it,

312
00:26:10,724 --> 00:26:12,476
but maybe we could help
each other out now.

313
00:26:14,770 --> 00:26:16,730
I need one of the pieces
your father collected.

314
00:26:16,897 --> 00:26:18,148
Bronze piece, about this size,

315
00:26:18,148 --> 00:26:20,108
with a hole in it, off-center,
with a crystal.

316
00:26:20,108 --> 00:26:21,234
You know the one I mean?

317
00:26:21,317 --> 00:26:23,236
Yeah.

318
00:26:23,278 --> 00:26:24,487
I know it.

319
00:26:24,529 --> 00:26:25,655
Where's Abner?

320
00:26:26,656 --> 00:26:28,616
Where's Abner?

321
00:26:28,616 --> 00:26:29,867
Abner's dead.

322
00:26:35,205 --> 00:26:37,624
Marion, I'm sorry.

323
00:26:37,707 --> 00:26:40,752
Do you know what you did to me,
to my life?

324
00:26:40,752 --> 00:26:43,254
I can only say
I'm sorry so many times.

325
00:26:43,254 --> 00:26:45,006
Well, say it again, anyway.

326
00:26:45,131 --> 00:26:46,174
Sorry.

327
00:26:46,174 --> 00:26:47,842
Yeah, everybody's sorry.

328
00:26:48,009 --> 00:26:50,844
Abner was sorry for dragging me
all over this earth

329
00:26:50,928 --> 00:26:52,805
looking
for his little bits of junk.

330
00:26:52,888 --> 00:26:55,307
I'm sorry to still be
stuck in this dive.

331
00:26:55,307 --> 00:26:58,018
Everybody's sorry for something.

332
00:26:58,018 --> 00:27:00,145
It's a worthless bronze
medallion, Marion.

333
00:27:00,145 --> 00:27:01,354
You going to give it to me?

334
00:27:01,521 --> 00:27:02,522
Maybe.

335
00:27:02,605 --> 00:27:04,440
I don't know where it is.

336
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:07,860
Well, maybe you could find it.

337
00:27:07,943 --> 00:27:10,362
3,000 bucks.

338
00:27:10,404 --> 00:27:14,283
Well, that will get me back,
but not in style.

339
00:27:14,283 --> 00:27:17,202
I can get you another two
when we get to the States.

340
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:19,412
It's important, Marion.

341
00:27:19,496 --> 00:27:21,623
Trust me.

342
00:27:22,790 --> 00:27:24,584
You know the piece I mean?

343
00:27:24,751 --> 00:27:26,252
Do you know where it is?

344
00:27:29,713 --> 00:27:31,298
Come back tomorrow.

345
00:27:31,382 --> 00:27:33,509
Why?

346
00:27:33,592 --> 00:27:37,387
Because I said so, that's why.

347
00:27:43,893 --> 00:27:45,061
Ha!

348
00:27:45,186 --> 00:27:47,229
See you tomorrow, Indiana Jones.

349
00:28:55,042 --> 00:28:56,877
Good evening, Fraulein.

350
00:28:57,043 --> 00:28:59,212
The bar's closed.

351
00:28:59,212 --> 00:29:02,340
We... We are...

352
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:04,300
not thirsty.

353
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:05,635
What do you want?

354
00:29:05,802 --> 00:29:08,721
The same thing your friend
Dr. Jones wanted.

355
00:29:08,763 --> 00:29:11,265
Surely he told you
there would be

356
00:29:11,390 --> 00:29:13,058
other interested parties.

357
00:29:13,183 --> 00:29:15,560
Must've slipped his mind.

358
00:29:15,644 --> 00:29:19,230
The man is... nefarious.

359
00:29:19,272 --> 00:29:23,610
I hope, for your sake,
he has not yet acquired it.

360
00:29:23,693 --> 00:29:25,945
Why, are you willing
to offer more?

361
00:29:25,945 --> 00:29:28,864
Oh, almost certainly.

362
00:29:29,031 --> 00:29:30,908
Do you still have it?

363
00:29:36,204 --> 00:29:37,998
No.

364
00:29:38,081 --> 00:29:40,917
But I know where it is.

365
00:29:42,043 --> 00:29:44,712
Hey, how about a drink
for you and your men?

366
00:29:44,879 --> 00:29:49,842
Your fire is dying here.

367
00:29:49,842 --> 00:29:52,553
Why don't you tell me
where the piece is right now?

368
00:29:52,678 --> 00:29:54,888
Listen, Herr Mac...

369
00:29:56,139 --> 00:29:59,559
I don't know what kind of people
you're used to dealing with,

370
00:29:59,643 --> 00:30:02,061
but nobody tells me
what to do in my place.

371
00:30:02,187 --> 00:30:05,481
Fraulein Ravenwood,

372
00:30:05,606 --> 00:30:09,485
let me show you
what I am used to.

373
00:30:11,528 --> 00:30:14,907
Take your hands off me!

374
00:30:16,783 --> 00:30:18,827
Take your lousy hands off!

375
00:30:25,333 --> 00:30:26,375
Wait a minute.

376
00:30:26,417 --> 00:30:27,668
Wait, I... I can be reasonable.

377
00:30:27,835 --> 00:30:30,045
That time is passed.

378
00:30:30,087 --> 00:30:31,714
You don't need that.

379
00:30:33,674 --> 00:30:34,758
Wait...

380
00:30:36,426 --> 00:30:37,928
I'll tell you everything.

381
00:30:38,053 --> 00:30:42,223
Yes, I know you will.

382
00:30:47,645 --> 00:30:49,105
Let her go.

383
00:32:04,132 --> 00:32:05,091
Whiskey.

384
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:15,600
Shoot them.

385
00:32:15,726 --> 00:32:17,477
Shoot them both.

386
00:33:06,986 --> 00:33:08,821
My medallion!

387
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:19,038
Well, Jones, at least
you haven't forgotten

388
00:33:19,122 --> 00:33:20,873
how to show a lady a good time!

389
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,541
Boy, you're something!

390
00:33:22,541 --> 00:33:23,709
Yeah, I'll tell you what.

391
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:25,711
Until I get back my $5,000,

392
00:33:25,753 --> 00:33:27,880
you're going to get more
than you bargained for.

393
00:33:27,963 --> 00:33:31,091
I'm your goddamn partner!

394
00:34:08,333 --> 00:34:10,627
Cairo, city of the living.

395
00:34:10,711 --> 00:34:12,379
A paradise on earth.

396
00:34:14,297 --> 00:34:15,423
Silence!

397
00:34:15,507 --> 00:34:16,966
Why do you forget yourselves?

398
00:34:17,050 --> 00:34:18,009
What is this?

399
00:34:18,176 --> 00:34:20,636
Where did this animal come from?

400
00:34:23,848 --> 00:34:25,015
Oh... oh, no.

401
00:34:27,476 --> 00:34:29,102
Cute.

402
00:34:29,186 --> 00:34:31,146
What an adorable creature.

403
00:34:33,148 --> 00:34:35,275
Then it shall be welcome
in our house.

404
00:34:35,316 --> 00:34:37,819
Oh, well, no, you don't have to
keep it here just because of me.

405
00:34:45,993 --> 00:34:48,245
I knew the Germans
would hire you, Sallah.

406
00:34:48,245 --> 00:34:50,372
You're the best digger in Egypt.

407
00:34:50,414 --> 00:34:54,084
My services are entirely
inconsequential to them.

408
00:34:54,084 --> 00:34:57,462
They've hired or shanghaied
every digger in Cairo.

409
00:34:57,462 --> 00:34:59,213
The excavation is enormous.

410
00:34:59,213 --> 00:35:03,175
They hire only strong backs
and they pay pennies for them.

411
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:06,428
It's as if the pharaohs
had returned.

412
00:35:06,553 --> 00:35:08,222
When did they find the map room?

413
00:35:08,263 --> 00:35:09,890
Three days ago.

414
00:35:09,973 --> 00:35:11,850
They have not one brain
among them.

415
00:35:11,850 --> 00:35:14,185
Except one.

416
00:35:14,352 --> 00:35:16,438
He is very clever.
He's a French archaeologist.

417
00:35:18,398 --> 00:35:20,024
What's his name?

418
00:35:20,191 --> 00:35:21,442
They call him ''Bellosh.''

419
00:35:27,865 --> 00:35:30,784
Belloq. Belloq.

420
00:35:30,784 --> 00:35:33,578
The Germans have
a great advantage over us.

421
00:35:33,703 --> 00:35:36,831
They are near to discovering
the Well of Souls.

422
00:35:36,998 --> 00:35:41,294
Well, they're not
going to find it without this.

423
00:35:41,460 --> 00:35:44,130
Who can tell us
about these markings?

424
00:35:47,007 --> 00:35:49,343
Perhaps a man I know
can help us.

425
00:35:50,719 --> 00:35:52,262
Indy...

426
00:35:54,681 --> 00:35:56,850
there is something
that troubles me.

427
00:35:56,975 --> 00:36:00,019
What is it?

428
00:36:00,019 --> 00:36:01,979
The Ark.

429
00:36:02,104 --> 00:36:04,398
If it is there, at Tanis,

430
00:36:04,398 --> 00:36:07,818
then it is something that man
was not meant to disturb.

431
00:36:07,901 --> 00:36:10,821
Death has always surrounded it.

432
00:36:10,946 --> 00:36:13,198
It is not of this earth.

433
00:36:13,198 --> 00:36:15,033
Do we need the monkey, huh?

434
00:36:15,116 --> 00:36:16,326
I'm surprised at you, Jones-

435
00:36:16,493 --> 00:36:19,078
talking that way about our baby.

436
00:36:19,203 --> 00:36:20,746
He's got your looks, too.

437
00:36:20,830 --> 00:36:21,789
And your brains.

438
00:36:21,914 --> 00:36:23,749
Oops!

439
00:36:23,749 --> 00:36:24,917
I noticed that.

440
00:36:25,042 --> 00:36:27,544
She's a smart little thing--
smart.

441
00:36:30,255 --> 00:36:31,506
Hey!

442
00:36:31,631 --> 00:36:32,716
Hey, where you going?

443
00:36:32,883 --> 00:36:34,634
She'll be all right.
Have a date.

444
00:36:38,554 --> 00:36:39,722
Come on. Come on.

445
00:36:39,806 --> 00:36:40,681
Okay...

446
00:36:40,765 --> 00:36:41,724
Marion.

447
00:36:41,766 --> 00:36:42,725
What's this?

448
00:36:42,808 --> 00:36:44,185
It's a date.

449
00:36:44,268 --> 00:36:45,811
You eat 'em.

450
00:37:34,689 --> 00:37:36,941
How come you haven't found some
nice girl to settle down with,

451
00:37:37,066 --> 00:37:39,068
raise eight or nine kids,
like your friend Sallah?

452
00:37:39,068 --> 00:37:40,111
Who says I haven't?

453
00:37:42,196 --> 00:37:43,280
I do.

454
00:37:43,447 --> 00:37:45,282
Dad had you figured
a long time ago.

455
00:37:54,582 --> 00:37:55,792
He said you were a bum.

456
00:37:55,959 --> 00:37:57,418
Oh, he's being generous.

457
00:37:57,418 --> 00:37:59,462
The most gifted bum
he ever trained.

458
00:37:59,462 --> 00:38:01,464
You know, he loved you
like a son.

459
00:38:01,464 --> 00:38:03,466
Took a hell of a lot
for you to alienate him.

460
00:38:03,507 --> 00:38:04,717
Not much, just you.

461
00:38:22,817 --> 00:38:23,984
Marion, get out of here!

462
00:38:24,068 --> 00:38:25,027
Duck!

463
00:39:06,732 --> 00:39:08,692
Right.

464
00:39:51,023 --> 00:39:53,066
Shh! Shh!

465
00:39:58,988 --> 00:40:00,448
Marion!

466
00:40:20,883 --> 00:40:22,843
Help! Over here, Indy!

467
00:40:22,927 --> 00:40:24,637
Get out of the way!

468
00:40:24,637 --> 00:40:26,096
Move! Move it!

469
00:40:27,556 --> 00:40:28,599
Help me!

470
00:40:33,812 --> 00:40:35,355
You can't do this to me!

471
00:40:35,438 --> 00:40:37,315
I'm an American!

472
00:40:37,315 --> 00:40:39,025
Indy!

473
00:40:42,945 --> 00:40:44,405
Indiana Jones!

474
00:40:44,572 --> 00:40:45,781
Help me, Jones!

475
00:41:06,634 --> 00:41:07,593
Jones!

476
00:41:07,634 --> 00:41:08,594
Marion!

477
00:41:12,764 --> 00:41:14,432
Indy!

478
00:41:56,387 --> 00:41:58,056
Marion...

479
00:42:35,757 --> 00:42:37,425
Dr. Jones.

480
00:43:04,283 --> 00:43:05,576
You looking for me?

481
00:43:14,334 --> 00:43:16,169
Belloq.

482
00:43:16,252 --> 00:43:17,712
Good afternoon, Dr. Jones.

483
00:43:17,712 --> 00:43:19,630
I ought to kill you right now.

484
00:43:19,797 --> 00:43:22,300
Not a very private place
for a murder.

485
00:43:23,384 --> 00:43:26,262
Well, these Arabs don't care
if we kill each other.

486
00:43:26,262 --> 00:43:29,389
They're not going
to interfere in our business.

487
00:43:29,431 --> 00:43:32,309
It was not I who brought
the girl into this business.

488
00:43:32,392 --> 00:43:34,519
Please, sit down
before you fall down.

489
00:43:34,561 --> 00:43:37,188
We can at least behave
like civilized people.

490
00:43:48,031 --> 00:43:50,200
I see your taste in friends
remains consistent.

491
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:53,370
How odd that it should end
this way for us,

492
00:43:53,370 --> 00:43:56,289
after so many
stimulating encounters.

493
00:43:56,414 --> 00:43:58,166
I almost regret it.

494
00:43:58,207 --> 00:43:59,834
Where shall I find
a new adversary

495
00:43:59,834 --> 00:44:01,794
so close to my own level?

496
00:44:01,877 --> 00:44:03,838
Try the local sewer.

497
00:44:06,340 --> 00:44:09,426
You and I are very much alike.

498
00:44:09,426 --> 00:44:11,720
Archaeology is our religion,

499
00:44:11,887 --> 00:44:16,349
yet we have both fallen
from the purer faith.

500
00:44:16,516 --> 00:44:19,852
Our methods have not differed
as much as you pretend.

501
00:44:19,977 --> 00:44:23,397
I am a shadowy
reflection of you.

502
00:44:23,397 --> 00:44:26,233
lt would take only a nudge
to make you like me,

503
00:44:26,317 --> 00:44:28,402
to push you out of the light.

504
00:44:28,444 --> 00:44:31,988
Now you're getting nasty.

505
00:44:32,155 --> 00:44:34,199
You know it's true.

506
00:44:34,324 --> 00:44:36,159
How nice.

507
00:44:36,326 --> 00:44:38,202
Look at this.

508
00:44:38,286 --> 00:44:40,037
It's worthless.

509
00:44:40,204 --> 00:44:42,581
Ten dollars
from a vendor in the street.

510
00:44:42,581 --> 00:44:43,708
But I take it,

511
00:44:43,833 --> 00:44:45,501
I bury it in the sand
for a thousand years,

512
00:44:45,501 --> 00:44:49,254
it becomes priceless...
like the Ark.

513
00:44:49,463 --> 00:44:51,214
Men will kill for it.

514
00:44:51,340 --> 00:44:53,884
Men like you and me.

515
00:44:54,050 --> 00:44:57,136
What about your boss,
der Fuehrer?

516
00:44:57,136 --> 00:45:00,723
I thought he was waiting
to take possession.

517
00:45:00,723 --> 00:45:03,434
All in good time.

518
00:45:03,434 --> 00:45:05,895
When I am finished with it.

519
00:45:05,936 --> 00:45:09,523
Jones, do you realize
what the Ark is?

520
00:45:09,690 --> 00:45:11,525
It's a transmitter.

521
00:45:11,650 --> 00:45:14,444
It's a radio
for speaking to God.

522
00:45:14,444 --> 00:45:16,112
And it's within my reach.

523
00:45:17,822 --> 00:45:21,701
You want to talk to God?

524
00:45:21,742 --> 00:45:23,494
Let's go see Him together.

525
00:45:23,661 --> 00:45:25,412
I've got nothing better to do.

526
00:45:26,580 --> 00:45:29,208
Uncle Indy, come back home now!

527
00:45:31,168 --> 00:45:32,210
Uncle Indy!

528
00:45:33,461 --> 00:45:35,046
Next time, Indiana Jones,

529
00:45:35,130 --> 00:45:37,590
it'll take more than children
to save you.

530
00:45:39,050 --> 00:45:40,468
Uncle Indy!

531
00:45:54,481 --> 00:45:56,066
I thought I would
find you there.

532
00:45:56,149 --> 00:45:58,359
Better than the United
States Marines, eh?

533
00:46:07,701 --> 00:46:09,077
Marion's dead.

534
00:46:09,244 --> 00:46:10,495
Yes, I know.

535
00:46:10,537 --> 00:46:12,664
And me! And me!

536
00:46:12,747 --> 00:46:14,291
I'm sorry.

537
00:46:14,416 --> 00:46:16,167
Life goes on, Indy.

538
00:46:16,167 --> 00:46:18,086
There is the proof.

539
00:46:20,088 --> 00:46:21,923
Uh-oh.

540
00:46:22,006 --> 00:46:23,424
I have much to tell you.

541
00:46:23,466 --> 00:46:26,093
First we will take them home,

542
00:46:26,176 --> 00:46:27,636
and then I will take you
to the old man.

543
00:47:18,725 --> 00:47:20,935
I can't figure out
how Belloq did it.

544
00:47:21,060 --> 00:47:23,479
Where'd he get a copy
of the headpiece?

545
00:47:23,521 --> 00:47:26,774
There are no pictures,
no duplicates of it anywhere.

546
00:47:26,899 --> 00:47:29,818
I tell you only what I saw
with my own eyes:

547
00:47:29,902 --> 00:47:31,278
A headpiece like that one,

548
00:47:31,278 --> 00:47:33,530
except round the edges,
which were rougher.

549
00:47:33,530 --> 00:47:35,657
In the center, the Frenchman
had embedded a crystal,

550
00:47:35,740 --> 00:47:40,578
and... and surrounding
the crystal, on one side,

551
00:47:40,620 --> 00:47:42,330
there were raised markings,
just like that one.

552
00:47:44,290 --> 00:47:47,126
They made their calculations
in the map room?

553
00:47:47,209 --> 00:47:48,585
This morning.

554
00:47:48,585 --> 00:47:50,879
Belloq and the boss German,
Dietrich.

555
00:47:50,962 --> 00:47:53,548
When they came out
of the map room,

556
00:47:53,632 --> 00:47:56,009
they gave us a new spot
in which to dig,

557
00:47:56,050 --> 00:47:58,761
out away from the camp.

558
00:47:58,761 --> 00:48:00,721
The Well of the Souls, huh?

559
00:48:00,888 --> 00:48:04,767
Come, come, look.
Look here... look.

560
00:48:04,809 --> 00:48:06,268
Sit down.

561
00:48:06,435 --> 00:48:07,978
Come, sit down.

562
00:48:07,978 --> 00:48:09,938
What is it?

563
00:48:10,063 --> 00:48:12,274
This is a warning

564
00:48:12,357 --> 00:48:14,776
not to disturb
the Ark of the Covenant.

565
00:48:14,776 --> 00:48:16,444
What about the height
of the staff, though?

566
00:48:16,528 --> 00:48:17,529
Did Belloq get it off of here?

567
00:48:17,529 --> 00:48:18,613
Yes.

568
00:48:18,613 --> 00:48:20,073
It is here.

569
00:48:20,073 --> 00:48:21,908
This were the old way,

570
00:48:22,033 --> 00:48:24,410
this mean six kadam high.

571
00:48:24,535 --> 00:48:25,703
-About 72 inches.
-Wait!

572
00:48:29,206 --> 00:48:32,125
''And take back one kadam

573
00:48:32,292 --> 00:48:36,087
to honor the Hebrew God
whose Ark this is.''

574
00:48:48,265 --> 00:48:50,267
You said their headpiece
only had markings on one side.

575
00:48:50,267 --> 00:48:52,144
Are you absolutely sure?

576
00:48:54,104 --> 00:48:55,814
Belloq's staff is too long.

577
00:48:55,897 --> 00:48:58,650
They're digging
in the wrong place.

578
00:49:00,360 --> 00:49:02,404
I am the monarch of the sea

579
00:49:02,571 --> 00:49:04,364
I am the ruler of the..

580
00:49:15,332 --> 00:49:17,042
Bad dates.

581
00:49:32,181 --> 00:49:34,350
I told you not to be premature

582
00:49:34,392 --> 00:49:36,769
in your communiqu?to Berlin.

583
00:49:36,810 --> 00:49:40,063
Archaeology is not
an exact science.

584
00:49:40,189 --> 00:49:42,232
It does not deal
in time schedules.

585
00:49:42,357 --> 00:49:44,359
The f端hrer is not
a patient man.

586
00:49:44,401 --> 00:49:47,862
He demands constant reports,
and he expects progress.

587
00:49:47,862 --> 00:49:49,447
You led me to believe...

588
00:49:49,530 --> 00:49:50,948
Nothing!
I made no promises.

589
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:52,992
I only said
it looked very favorable.

590
00:49:53,117 --> 00:49:56,328
Besides, with the information
in our possession,

591
00:49:56,328 --> 00:49:58,288
my calculations were correct.

592
00:49:58,288 --> 00:50:00,207
Boy, they're not kidding,
are they?

593
00:50:02,084 --> 00:50:04,044
What time does the sun
hit the map room?

594
00:50:04,127 --> 00:50:06,087
At about 9:00 in the morning.

595
00:50:06,254 --> 00:50:07,297
Not much time, then.

596
00:50:07,338 --> 00:50:10,216
Where are they digging
for the Well of the Souls?

597
00:50:10,258 --> 00:50:13,511
On that ridge...
but the map room's over there.

598
00:50:13,636 --> 00:50:14,887
Let's go, come on.

599
00:54:21,446 --> 00:54:22,989
Sallah.

600
00:54:24,115 --> 00:54:25,825
Sallah!

601
00:54:33,666 --> 00:54:34,667
They're here.

602
00:54:45,802 --> 00:54:47,220
Please, my friend,
what is the matter?

603
00:54:47,220 --> 00:54:49,013
I fetch the water.
I shall get it for you.

604
00:54:51,724 --> 00:54:53,684
If you want water,
I will get you water.

605
00:54:53,893 --> 00:54:55,060
No problem, no problem.

606
00:55:09,115 --> 00:55:10,491
I thought you were dead.

607
00:55:10,533 --> 00:55:12,368
You must have switched baskets.

608
00:55:16,705 --> 00:55:17,998
Are you hurt?

609
00:55:17,998 --> 00:55:20,709
No. You have to get me
out of here, quick.

610
00:55:20,792 --> 00:55:23,044
They're gonna be back
at any minute.

611
00:55:23,211 --> 00:55:24,004
Cut me loose.

612
00:55:24,171 --> 00:55:25,171
Quick.

613
00:55:25,297 --> 00:55:27,632
They keep asking about you.
What you know.

614
00:55:32,470 --> 00:55:33,846
What's wrong?

615
00:55:33,929 --> 00:55:34,889
Cut me loose.

616
00:55:34,972 --> 00:55:36,348
I know where the Ark is, Marion.

617
00:55:36,348 --> 00:55:38,600
The Ark's here?

618
00:55:38,767 --> 00:55:40,310
I'm coming with you, Jones.
Get me out of here!

619
00:55:40,435 --> 00:55:41,770
Cut me loose!
You can't leave me here!

620
00:55:41,812 --> 00:55:42,771
If I take you out of here now,

621
00:55:42,938 --> 00:55:44,439
they'll start combing
the place for us.

622
00:55:44,439 --> 00:55:45,899
Jones, you've got to get me
out of here!

623
00:55:45,899 --> 00:55:48,610
Come on, Jones, are you crazy?!

624
00:55:48,776 --> 00:55:50,153
Marion, I hate to do this,

625
00:55:50,319 --> 00:55:52,780
but if you don't sit
still and keep quiet,

626
00:55:52,780 --> 00:55:55,199
this whole thing
is going to be shot.

627
00:55:56,659 --> 00:55:58,202
I'll be back to get you.

628
00:55:58,369 --> 00:56:00,078
Jones, what's the matter?

629
00:56:45,745 --> 00:56:47,330
That's it.

630
00:56:47,330 --> 00:56:48,456
Who knows?

631
00:56:48,581 --> 00:56:50,583
Perhaps the Ark is still waiting

632
00:56:50,583 --> 00:56:53,044
in some antechamber
for us to discover.

633
00:56:53,127 --> 00:56:57,006
Perhaps there's some vital
bit of evidence which eludes us.

634
00:56:57,006 --> 00:56:58,090
Perhaps...

635
00:56:58,090 --> 00:56:59,842
Perhaps the girl can help us.

636
00:56:59,842 --> 00:57:01,176
My feeling exactly.

637
00:57:01,176 --> 00:57:04,429
She was in possession
of the original piece for years.

638
00:57:04,512 --> 00:57:06,806
She may know much,
if properly motivated.

639
00:57:06,806 --> 00:57:09,350
I tell you,
the girl knows nothing.

640
00:57:10,601 --> 00:57:12,478
I'm surprised
to find you squeamish.

641
00:57:12,562 --> 00:57:14,021
That is not your reputation.

642
00:57:14,105 --> 00:57:15,523
But it needn't concern you.

643
00:57:15,564 --> 00:57:18,108
I have the perfect man
for this kind of work.

644
00:57:22,863 --> 00:57:25,407
Heil Hitler.

645
00:58:47,774 --> 00:58:49,025
Indy! Here!

646
00:58:49,067 --> 00:58:50,985
We've hit stone!

647
00:58:54,113 --> 00:58:55,656
Clear it off.

648
00:58:55,656 --> 00:58:57,116
Come on, find the edges.

649
00:59:14,048 --> 00:59:15,633
Good, good, good.

650
00:59:15,674 --> 00:59:17,301
You see, Indy? You see?

651
00:59:17,343 --> 00:59:19,261
Okay, bring the pry bars in.

652
00:59:19,261 --> 00:59:21,138
As a team, boys! As a team!

653
00:59:23,181 --> 00:59:24,057
Push!

654
00:59:29,354 --> 00:59:30,521
Get 'em in there.

655
00:59:30,646 --> 00:59:31,481
Get 'em under.

656
00:59:31,522 --> 00:59:32,440
Good, good, that's it.

657
00:59:32,607 --> 00:59:33,649
Watch your toes.

658
00:59:41,156 --> 00:59:42,908
Carefully, carefully!

659
00:59:53,959 --> 00:59:56,587
Sorry, Indy.

660
00:59:57,755 --> 01:00:00,007
Indy...

661
01:00:00,007 --> 01:00:02,634
why does the floor move?

662
01:00:03,969 --> 01:00:06,096
Give me your torch.

663
01:00:36,498 --> 01:00:38,375
Snakes.

664
01:00:38,459 --> 01:00:39,751
Why did it have to be snakes?

665
01:00:43,505 --> 01:00:46,508
Asps.

666
01:00:46,508 --> 01:00:49,093
Very dangerous.

667
01:00:49,093 --> 01:00:50,303
You go first.

668
01:01:09,779 --> 01:01:11,823
If you're trying
to escape on foot,

669
01:01:11,823 --> 01:01:15,201
the desert is three weeks
in every direction,

670
01:01:15,284 --> 01:01:17,077
so please, eat something.

671
01:01:24,167 --> 01:01:26,211
I must apologize
for their treatment of you.

672
01:01:26,294 --> 01:01:27,462
Yeah. Whose idea was it?

673
01:01:27,587 --> 01:01:28,671
No food, no water.

674
01:01:28,713 --> 01:01:30,840
What kind of people
are these friends of yours?

675
01:01:30,882 --> 01:01:33,968
At this particular time
and place, to do my work,

676
01:01:33,968 --> 01:01:35,803
they are necessary evils.

677
01:01:35,928 --> 01:01:37,471
They're not my friends.

678
01:01:37,471 --> 01:01:39,807
However, with the
right connections,

679
01:01:39,807 --> 01:01:41,767
even in this part of the world,

680
01:01:41,767 --> 01:01:44,936
we are not entirely uncivilized.

681
01:01:46,479 --> 01:01:48,356
It's beautiful.

682
01:01:48,439 --> 01:01:50,900
I would very much like
to see you in it.

683
01:01:53,027 --> 01:01:55,237
I'll bet you would.

684
01:01:59,116 --> 01:02:01,076
All right.

685
01:02:08,958 --> 01:02:11,085
What do you got to drink
around here?

686
01:02:13,838 --> 01:02:15,965
We don't have much time.

687
01:02:16,048 --> 01:02:17,966
Soon they will come to harm you,

688
01:02:18,008 --> 01:02:20,010
and I will not be able
to stop them,

689
01:02:20,135 --> 01:02:22,596
unless you are able
to give me something

690
01:02:22,596 --> 01:02:24,598
to placate them.

691
01:02:24,598 --> 01:02:27,642
Some, uh, piece
of information...

692
01:02:27,642 --> 01:02:30,436
which I can use
to protect you from them.

693
01:02:30,561 --> 01:02:32,772
I've already told you
everything I know.

694
01:02:32,855 --> 01:02:35,566
I have no loyalty to Jones.

695
01:02:35,691 --> 01:02:38,193
He's brought me
nothing but trouble.

696
01:02:44,574 --> 01:02:46,534
Marion, you are beautiful.

697
01:02:51,497 --> 01:02:54,750
I don't think
we need a chaperone.

698
01:02:57,920 --> 01:02:59,296
Steadily.

699
01:02:59,296 --> 01:03:01,340
Steadily. Whoa!

700
01:03:03,633 --> 01:03:04,759
Down...

701
01:03:04,759 --> 01:03:05,885
Down.. Whoa.

702
01:03:05,885 --> 01:03:07,053
Carefully, carefully!

703
01:03:07,178 --> 01:03:09,305
You all right, Indy?

704
01:03:12,099 --> 01:03:16,979
Now gently, boys.
Gently, gently!

705
01:03:25,153 --> 01:03:25,904
Whoa...

706
01:03:35,913 --> 01:03:37,289
I told you it will be all right.

707
01:03:53,888 --> 01:03:55,347
Huh...

708
01:04:03,563 --> 01:04:05,440
Sallah, get down here!

709
01:04:24,708 --> 01:04:26,626
You pour.

710
01:06:20,063 --> 01:06:21,898
Oh, that's good.

711
01:06:25,277 --> 01:06:26,569
Whoops.

712
01:06:32,992 --> 01:06:34,535
What is this stuff, Rene?

713
01:06:36,287 --> 01:06:37,871
I grew up with this.

714
01:06:39,373 --> 01:06:40,874
It's my family label.

715
01:07:10,318 --> 01:07:13,738
Well... I have to be
going now, Rene.

716
01:07:15,531 --> 01:07:18,742
I like you, Rene, very much.

717
01:07:18,742 --> 01:07:21,453
Perhaps we'll meet someday
under better circumstances.

718
01:07:25,749 --> 01:07:27,917
We meet again, Fraulein.

719
01:07:29,460 --> 01:07:31,754
You Americans,
you're all the same.

720
01:07:34,006 --> 01:07:37,009
Always overdressing
for the wrong occasions.

721
01:08:07,620 --> 01:08:09,956
Now...

722
01:08:12,416 --> 01:08:15,127
what shall we talk about?

723
01:09:32,823 --> 01:09:35,743
All right... take it up!

724
01:09:35,868 --> 01:09:37,870
Easy!

725
01:09:39,371 --> 01:09:41,206
You're as stubborn as that girl.

726
01:09:41,290 --> 01:09:43,750
You like her too much, I think.

727
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:48,588
Your methods of archaeology
are too primitive for me.

728
01:09:48,796 --> 01:09:52,758
You would use a bulldozer
to find a... China cup.

729
01:09:57,179 --> 01:09:59,014
Shliemann! Wake your men!

730
01:09:59,014 --> 01:10:01,224
Indy, the torches
are burning out.

731
01:10:01,308 --> 01:10:03,185
Go on, get out of here.

732
01:10:03,351 --> 01:10:05,145
Hyah!

733
01:10:22,994 --> 01:10:24,162
Sallah!

734
01:10:24,246 --> 01:10:25,247
Hello!

735
01:10:26,206 --> 01:10:27,207
Hello!

736
01:10:27,207 --> 01:10:29,876
Why, Dr. Jones,
whatever are you doing

737
01:10:29,959 --> 01:10:32,503
in such a nasty place?

738
01:10:32,545 --> 01:10:34,547
Why don't you come on down here!
I'll show you!

739
01:10:34,547 --> 01:10:35,548
Thank you, my friend,

740
01:10:35,548 --> 01:10:37,966
but I think we are all
very comfortable up here.

741
01:10:38,175 --> 01:10:39,426
That's right, isn't it?

742
01:10:40,510 --> 01:10:42,804
Yes, we are very comfortable
up here.

743
01:10:44,264 --> 01:10:46,141
So, once again, Jones,

744
01:10:46,224 --> 01:10:49,352
what was briefly yours
is now mine.

745
01:10:49,435 --> 01:10:51,979
What a fitting end
to your life's pursuits.

746
01:10:51,979 --> 01:10:54,482
You're about to become
a permanent addition

747
01:10:54,690 --> 01:10:56,150
to this archaeological find.

748
01:10:56,233 --> 01:10:57,484
Who knows?

749
01:10:57,610 --> 01:10:59,695
In a thousand years,
even you may be worth something.

750
01:11:02,155 --> 01:11:03,865
Son of a bitch.

751
01:11:03,865 --> 01:11:05,825
I'm afraid we must be
going now, Dr. Jones.

752
01:11:05,909 --> 01:11:08,203
Our prize is awaited in Berlin.

753
01:11:08,286 --> 01:11:10,163
But I do not wish to leave you

754
01:11:10,329 --> 01:11:12,582
down in that awful place
all alone.

755
01:11:12,665 --> 01:11:14,500
Slimy pig, you let me go!

756
01:11:14,542 --> 01:11:15,751
Stop it!

757
01:11:18,420 --> 01:11:20,005
Marion!

758
01:11:20,005 --> 01:11:21,048
Hang on.

759
01:11:22,341 --> 01:11:23,341
Don't...

760
01:11:23,425 --> 01:11:25,010
-Indy!
-Don't fall!

761
01:11:25,093 --> 01:11:27,429
Marion, I got you!
I got you! I got you!

762
01:11:31,140 --> 01:11:33,434
You traitor!
You get your hands off of me!

763
01:11:41,358 --> 01:11:42,359
Snakes!

764
01:11:43,985 --> 01:11:45,487
Oh, sh... oh, at your feet!

765
01:11:47,030 --> 01:11:48,239
The girl was mine!

766
01:11:48,239 --> 01:11:49,198
She's of no use to us.

767
01:11:49,282 --> 01:11:51,325
Only our mission
for the f端hrer matters.

768
01:11:53,661 --> 01:11:55,788
I wonder sometimes, Monsieur,

769
01:11:55,871 --> 01:11:58,248
if you have that
clearly in mind.

770
01:11:58,248 --> 01:12:00,375
It was not to be, ch辿rie.

771
01:12:00,375 --> 01:12:03,086
You bastards!
I'll get you for this!

772
01:12:03,211 --> 01:12:06,006
Indiana Jones...

773
01:12:06,089 --> 01:12:07,173
adieu.

774
01:12:19,726 --> 01:12:21,645
No!

775
01:12:30,945 --> 01:12:32,071
Take this.

776
01:12:32,238 --> 01:12:33,906
Wave it at anything
that slithers.

777
01:12:34,031 --> 01:12:35,157
Thank you.

778
01:12:35,324 --> 01:12:37,868
Oh, my God, this whole
place is slithering.

779
01:12:40,996 --> 01:12:42,080
Indy!

780
01:12:42,247 --> 01:12:44,791
Ow! Jesus!

781
01:12:46,418 --> 01:12:49,003
Where did you get this?
From him?

782
01:12:49,087 --> 01:12:50,421
I was trying to escape.

783
01:12:50,505 --> 01:12:51,464
No thanks to you.

784
01:12:51,506 --> 01:12:53,007
How hard were you trying?

785
01:12:53,007 --> 01:12:54,133
Well, where the hell were you?

786
01:12:54,342 --> 01:12:55,509
Watch it, watch it.

787
01:12:55,634 --> 01:12:56,844
What are you doing?

788
01:12:56,969 --> 01:12:58,512
For the fire!

789
01:13:00,556 --> 01:13:02,265
How the hell are we going
to get out of here?

790
01:13:02,432 --> 01:13:03,934
I'm working on it!
I'm working on it!

791
01:13:03,934 --> 01:13:05,644
Well, whatever you're
doing, do it faster.

792
01:13:09,856 --> 01:13:11,232
Ah...

793
01:13:11,232 --> 01:13:13,192
Where are you going?

794
01:13:13,192 --> 01:13:14,693
Through that wall.

795
01:13:14,693 --> 01:13:17,112
Just get ready to run,
whatever happens to me.

796
01:13:17,237 --> 01:13:18,781
What do you mean by that?

797
01:13:30,249 --> 01:13:32,710
Indy!

798
01:13:32,793 --> 01:13:35,629
Damn it! Don't you leave me
down here by myself!

799
01:14:00,485 --> 01:14:02,237
Indy!

800
01:14:02,320 --> 01:14:03,405
Here we go!

801
01:14:03,488 --> 01:14:04,447
Get ready!

802
01:14:04,489 --> 01:14:08,368
Indy, the torch is going out!

803
01:14:49,364 --> 01:14:50,823
Indy?

804
01:15:11,134 --> 01:15:12,885
Marion!

805
01:15:12,885 --> 01:15:15,429
Look. Look.

