01:15:53,506 --> 01:15:55,299
They're going to fly it
out of here.

807
01:15:55,341 --> 01:15:56,717
When that Ark gets loaded,

808
01:15:56,759 --> 01:15:58,969
we're already going
to be on the plane.

809
01:16:03,723 --> 01:16:07,519
Ah, monsieur, let us toast
our success in the desert.

810
01:16:07,685 --> 01:16:08,937
To the Ark.

811
01:16:09,020 --> 01:16:10,897
When we are very far
from here.

812
01:16:10,980 --> 01:16:12,648
That will do.

813
01:17:04,863 --> 01:17:09,242
Hey, you now.. come here!

814
01:17:09,409 --> 01:17:10,785
Come here!

815
01:18:15,970 --> 01:18:17,304
Indy!

816
01:19:08,226 --> 01:19:10,353
Stay with the Ark!
Stay with the Ark!

817
01:19:15,983 --> 01:19:16,901
Look out!

818
01:19:27,702 --> 01:19:29,120
Oh, my God.

819
01:19:29,203 --> 01:19:29,912
Marion.

820
01:19:29,912 --> 01:19:32,707
In here! Up here!

821
01:19:35,501 --> 01:19:36,627
Indy, come on!

822
01:19:36,627 --> 01:19:37,670
Hold on!

823
01:19:37,711 --> 01:19:39,713
Move up!
It's gonna blow up!

824
01:19:41,590 --> 01:19:44,843
It's stuck! Indy!

825
01:19:46,052 --> 01:19:47,679
I can't push it off!

826
01:20:17,539 --> 01:20:18,457
It's stuck!

827
01:20:18,457 --> 01:20:19,958
-Turn it! Turn it!
-It's stuck!

828
01:20:19,958 --> 01:20:21,209
Turn it there!

829
01:20:21,209 --> 01:20:22,753
Never mind!
Get back! Get back!

830
01:20:44,356 --> 01:20:46,775
Get the Ark away from
this place immediately.

831
01:20:46,900 --> 01:20:48,735
Have it put on the truck.

832
01:20:48,735 --> 01:20:50,194
We'll fly it out of Cairo.

833
01:20:50,194 --> 01:20:53,030
And Gobler, I want
plenty of protection.

834
01:20:59,620 --> 01:21:01,204
Jones.

835
01:21:07,085 --> 01:21:08,336
Holy smoke, my friends,

836
01:21:08,503 --> 01:21:10,213
I... I'm so pleased
you're not dead!

837
01:21:12,131 --> 01:21:13,591
Indy, Indy, we have no time.

838
01:21:13,633 --> 01:21:14,842
If you still want the Ark,

839
01:21:15,050 --> 01:21:17,428
it is being loaded
onto a truck for Cairo.

840
01:21:17,511 --> 01:21:19,430
Truck?

841
01:21:19,430 --> 01:21:20,681
What truck?

842
01:21:47,997 --> 01:21:49,082
Let's go!

843
01:21:57,548 --> 01:21:59,758
Get back to Cairo.

844
01:21:59,842 --> 01:22:01,968
Get us some transport
to England-

845
01:22:02,010 --> 01:22:04,888
boat, plane, anything.

846
01:22:05,096 --> 01:22:06,097
Meet me at Omar's.

847
01:22:06,097 --> 01:22:07,015
Be ready for me.

848
01:22:07,140 --> 01:22:08,224
I'm going after that truck.

849
01:22:08,224 --> 01:22:09,267
How?

850
01:22:09,267 --> 01:22:10,268
I don't know.

851
01:22:10,268 --> 01:22:11,727
I'm making this up as I go.

852
01:25:49,135 --> 01:25:50,678
Ew!

853
01:28:12,600 --> 01:28:13,517
He's there!

854
01:29:06,149 --> 01:29:07,942
Idiot! Idiot!

855
01:29:52,692 --> 01:29:54,860
Everything at last
has been arranged.

856
01:29:54,985 --> 01:29:56,195
The Ark?

857
01:29:56,320 --> 01:29:57,404
Is on board.

858
01:29:57,404 --> 01:29:59,198
Nothing is lacking,
now that you're here.

859
01:29:59,448 --> 01:30:00,616
Or what is left of you.

860
01:30:00,699 --> 01:30:01,658
You trust these guys?

861
01:30:01,783 --> 01:30:03,118
Yes.

862
01:30:03,118 --> 01:30:05,328
Mr. Katanga.

863
01:30:09,457 --> 01:30:12,084
Mr. Katanga,
these are my friends.

864
01:30:12,084 --> 01:30:13,919
They are my family.

865
01:30:14,086 --> 01:30:16,797
I will hear of it
if they are not treated well.

866
01:30:16,922 --> 01:30:19,925
My cabin is theirs.

867
01:30:19,967 --> 01:30:21,593
Mr. Jones...

868
01:30:21,802 --> 01:30:24,137
I've heard a lot about you, sir.

869
01:30:24,262 --> 01:30:27,307
Your appearance is exactly
the way I imagined.

870
01:30:32,353 --> 01:30:34,605
Good-bye.

871
01:30:35,981 --> 01:30:37,858
Look out for each other.

872
01:30:38,108 --> 01:30:40,235
I am already missing you.

873
01:30:42,487 --> 01:30:44,698
You're my good friend.

874
01:30:46,366 --> 01:30:48,493
Sallah.

875
01:30:51,829 --> 01:30:54,623
That is for Fayah...

876
01:30:54,707 --> 01:30:57,251
that is for your children...

877
01:30:57,251 --> 01:30:59,586
and this is for you.

878
01:31:04,424 --> 01:31:05,842
Thank you.

879
01:31:14,642 --> 01:31:19,521
A British tar is a soaring soul

880
01:31:19,605 --> 01:31:24,192
As free as a mountain bird

881
01:31:24,192 --> 01:31:27,862
His energetic fist
should be ready to...

882
01:31:30,406 --> 01:31:32,241
...a dictator...

883
01:31:38,831 --> 01:31:40,749
Where did you go?

884
01:31:40,791 --> 01:31:41,875
I'm cleaning up.

885
01:31:43,418 --> 01:31:45,420
Where'd you get that?

886
01:31:45,420 --> 01:31:46,880
From him.

887
01:31:46,880 --> 01:31:48,256
Who him?

888
01:31:48,339 --> 01:31:49,132
Katanga.

889
01:31:49,340 --> 01:31:51,259
l got a feeling
I'm not the first woman

890
01:31:51,300 --> 01:31:52,927
ever to travel
with these pirates.

891
01:31:52,969 --> 01:31:55,179
It's lovely.

892
01:31:55,179 --> 01:31:56,222
Yeah?

893
01:31:56,222 --> 01:31:57,139
Yeah.

894
01:31:57,139 --> 01:31:58,265
Really?

895
01:31:58,265 --> 01:32:00,058
Yeah.

896
01:32:11,277 --> 01:32:13,154
What'd you say?

897
01:32:20,035 --> 01:32:22,287
Wait... I don't need any help.

898
01:32:22,287 --> 01:32:23,955
You know you do.

899
01:32:25,749 --> 01:32:29,168
You're not the man
I knew ten years ago.

900
01:32:29,168 --> 01:32:33,756
It's not the years, honey,
it's the mileage.

901
01:32:37,176 --> 01:32:39,094
You are...

902
01:32:40,470 --> 01:32:42,055
Please, I don't need a nurse.

903
01:32:42,097 --> 01:32:43,557
-I just want to sleep.
-Don't be such a baby.

904
01:32:43,557 --> 01:32:44,641
Marion, leave me alone.

905
01:32:44,724 --> 01:32:46,101
-What is this here?
-Go away.

906
01:32:46,184 --> 01:32:48,436
Yes, it hurts.

907
01:32:48,603 --> 01:32:49,937
Ow!

908
01:32:50,063 --> 01:32:52,106
Well, goddamn it, Indy,
where doesn't it hurt?

909
01:32:53,733 --> 01:32:55,484
Here.

910
01:33:00,989 --> 01:33:02,491
Here.

911
01:33:10,998 --> 01:33:13,000
This isn't too bad.

912
01:33:22,509 --> 01:33:23,510
Here.

913
01:33:44,279 --> 01:33:45,280
Jones...

914
01:33:48,116 --> 01:33:50,118
Jones?

915
01:33:52,578 --> 01:33:56,332
We never seem to get
a break, do we?

916
01:34:22,689 --> 01:34:24,065
What is it?

917
01:34:24,232 --> 01:34:25,525
Engines have stopped.

918
01:34:25,525 --> 01:34:27,152
I'm going to go check.

919
01:34:37,828 --> 01:34:38,787
What's happening?

920
01:34:38,912 --> 01:34:40,164
We have most important friends.

921
01:34:40,164 --> 01:34:41,915
Holy shit.

922
01:34:43,583 --> 01:34:44,376
I sent my man for you.

923
01:34:44,376 --> 01:34:45,502
You and the girl must disappear.

924
01:34:45,543 --> 01:34:46,586
We have a place in the hold.

925
01:34:46,753 --> 01:34:47,295
Come on, go, go, go.

926
01:34:47,462 --> 01:34:48,254
Come on, go, my friend, go.

927
01:35:01,099 --> 01:35:03,518
Where is Dr. Jones?

928
01:35:03,518 --> 01:35:04,561
What's the big idea?

929
01:35:04,561 --> 01:35:05,812
Let go!

930
01:35:09,983 --> 01:35:12,652
Don't you touch me.

931
01:35:56,817 --> 01:35:58,569
What about Jones?

932
01:35:58,610 --> 01:36:01,029
There's no trace yet, sir.

933
01:36:01,029 --> 01:36:03,156
Jones is dead.

934
01:36:04,449 --> 01:36:06,659
I killed him.

935
01:36:06,826 --> 01:36:08,786
He was of no use to us.

936
01:36:08,786 --> 01:36:13,916
This girl, however, has certain
value where we're headed.

937
01:36:13,958 --> 01:36:16,460
She'll bring a very good price.

938
01:36:16,585 --> 01:36:17,544
Mmm?

939
01:36:17,628 --> 01:36:21,173
Herr Colonel,
that cargo you've taken-

940
01:36:21,173 --> 01:36:23,049
if it's your goal,
go in peace with it,

941
01:36:23,175 --> 01:36:24,342
but leave us the girl.

942
01:36:24,426 --> 01:36:26,302
It would reduce our loss
on this trip.

943
01:36:26,302 --> 01:36:27,929
Savage!

944
01:36:28,096 --> 01:36:31,724
You are not in the position
to ask for anything.

945
01:36:31,808 --> 01:36:33,684
We will take what we wish.

946
01:36:33,684 --> 01:36:35,352
And then decide whether or not

947
01:36:35,436 --> 01:36:37,563
to blow your ship
from the water.

948
01:36:40,691 --> 01:36:42,150
The girl goes with me.

949
01:36:42,150 --> 01:36:44,486
She'll be part
of my compensation.

950
01:36:44,486 --> 01:36:46,905
I'm sure your f端hrer
would approve.

951
01:36:47,030 --> 01:36:48,656
If she fails to please me,

952
01:36:48,656 --> 01:36:50,783
you may do with her as you wish.

953
01:36:50,867 --> 01:36:53,703
I will waste
no more time with her now.

954
01:36:53,703 --> 01:36:54,870
Excuse me.

955
01:37:11,302 --> 01:37:13,012
I can't find Mr. Jones, Captain.

956
01:37:13,095 --> 01:37:14,221
I've looked everywhere.

957
01:37:14,388 --> 01:37:16,891
He's got to be here somewhere.

958
01:37:16,932 --> 01:37:18,142
Look again.

959
01:37:19,935 --> 01:37:21,770
-I found him.
-Where?

960
01:37:21,770 --> 01:37:22,729
There.

961
01:39:48,988 --> 01:39:51,199
The altar has been
prepared in accordance

962
01:39:51,240 --> 01:39:53,159
with your radio instructions,
sir.

963
01:39:53,159 --> 01:39:54,160
Good.

964
01:39:54,285 --> 01:39:55,786
Take the Ark there immediately.

965
01:39:57,538 --> 01:39:59,206
Monsieur...

966
01:40:01,708 --> 01:40:03,794
I am uncomfortable
with the thought

967
01:40:03,877 --> 01:40:06,504
of this... Jewish ritual.

968
01:40:07,964 --> 01:40:10,383
Are you sure it's necessary?

969
01:40:10,383 --> 01:40:12,343
Let me ask you this:

970
01:40:12,343 --> 01:40:16,513
Would you be more comfortable
opening the Ark in Berlin,

971
01:40:16,597 --> 01:40:18,349
for your f端hrer?

972
01:40:18,474 --> 01:40:19,600
Finding out, only then,

973
01:40:19,808 --> 01:40:22,728
if the sacred pieces
of the Covenant are inside?

974
01:40:22,894 --> 01:40:23,895
Knowing, only then,

975
01:40:24,145 --> 01:40:25,939
whether you have accomplished
your mission,

976
01:40:26,106 --> 01:40:29,233
and obtained the one true Ark?

977
01:41:57,564 --> 01:41:58,857
Hello!

978
01:42:01,485 --> 01:42:02,527
Jones.

979
01:42:03,987 --> 01:42:05,363
Jones!

980
01:42:05,363 --> 01:42:07,407
I'm going to blow up the Ark,
Rene.

981
01:42:13,412 --> 01:42:17,583
Your persistence
surprises even me.

982
01:42:17,583 --> 01:42:20,085
You're going to give
mercenaries a bad name.

983
01:42:20,127 --> 01:42:22,754
Dr. Jones...

984
01:42:25,257 --> 01:42:27,717
surely you don't think you can
escape from this island.

985
01:42:27,884 --> 01:42:30,887
That depends on how reasonable
we're all willing to be.

986
01:42:31,012 --> 01:42:33,055
All I want is the girl.

987
01:42:37,226 --> 01:42:38,894
If we refuse?

988
01:42:38,977 --> 01:42:42,856
Then your f端hrer has no prize.

989
01:42:43,023 --> 01:42:44,274
Okay, stand back.

990
01:42:44,274 --> 01:42:45,567
All of you, stand back.

991
01:42:45,692 --> 01:42:47,235
Stand back.

992
01:42:47,235 --> 01:42:48,486
Okay, Jones.

993
01:42:48,486 --> 01:42:51,614
You win!

994
01:42:51,781 --> 01:42:53,157
Blow it up.

995
01:42:58,871 --> 01:43:00,122
Yes, blow it up!

996
01:43:02,332 --> 01:43:04,334
Blow it back to God.

997
01:43:04,459 --> 01:43:06,461
All your life has been spent

998
01:43:06,503 --> 01:43:09,005
in pursuit
of archaeological relics.

999
01:43:09,172 --> 01:43:13,592
Inside the Ark are treasures
beyond your wildest aspirations.

1000
01:43:13,759 --> 01:43:18,138
You want to see it open
as well as I.

1001
01:43:18,138 --> 01:43:20,432
Indiana...

1002
01:43:20,432 --> 01:43:24,728
we are simply passing
through history.

1003
01:43:24,811 --> 01:43:25,812
This...

1004
01:43:28,523 --> 01:43:30,191
This is history.

1005
01:43:39,408 --> 01:43:41,827
Do as you will.

1006
01:46:16,677 --> 01:46:19,096
Marion, don't look at it.

1007
01:46:19,096 --> 01:46:20,305
Shut your eyes, Marion.

1008
01:46:20,305 --> 01:46:22,099
Don't look at it,
no matter what happens.

1009
01:46:33,776 --> 01:46:36,278
Ah...

1010
01:46:50,375 --> 01:46:53,085
It's beautiful!

1011
01:47:03,261 --> 01:47:04,346
Indy?

1012
01:47:04,512 --> 01:47:05,639
Don't look, Marion!

1013
01:47:05,722 --> 01:47:07,098
Keep your eyes shut!

1014
01:48:25,295 --> 01:48:26,296
Marion.

1015
01:48:58,951 --> 01:49:01,953
You've done your country a
great service, and we thank you

1016
01:49:01,953 --> 01:49:06,416
and we trust you found
the settlement satisfactory.

1017
01:49:06,583 --> 01:49:07,584
Oh, the money's fine.

1018
01:49:07,584 --> 01:49:09,502
The situation's
totally unacceptable.

1019
01:49:09,502 --> 01:49:10,503
Well, gentlemen,

1020
01:49:10,503 --> 01:49:12,255
I guess that just about
wraps it up.

1021
01:49:12,255 --> 01:49:14,298
Where is the Ark?

1022
01:49:14,298 --> 01:49:17,384
I thought we'd settled that.

1023
01:49:17,551 --> 01:49:19,720
The Ark is somewhere very safe.

1024
01:49:19,761 --> 01:49:20,971
From whom?

1025
01:49:21,013 --> 01:49:24,099
The Ark is a source
of unspeakable power

1026
01:49:24,307 --> 01:49:26,351
and it has to be researched.

1027
01:49:26,351 --> 01:49:29,354
And it will be,
I assure you, Dr. Brody,

1028
01:49:29,520 --> 01:49:30,646
Dr. Jones.

1029
01:49:30,730 --> 01:49:34,316
We have top men
working on it right now.

1030
01:49:35,609 --> 01:49:36,819
Who?

1031
01:49:38,487 --> 01:49:40,906
Top men.

1032
01:49:43,950 --> 01:49:46,327
Hey, what happened?

1033
01:49:46,369 --> 01:49:47,412
You don't look very happy.

1034
01:49:47,579 --> 01:49:49,372
Fools. Bureaucratic fools.

1035
01:49:49,539 --> 01:49:50,540
What'd they say?

1036
01:49:50,665 --> 01:49:53,709
They don't know
what they've got there.

1037
01:49:53,834 --> 01:49:57,129
Well, I know what I've got here.

1038
01:49:57,254 --> 01:49:58,505
Come on.

1039
01:49:58,505 --> 01:49:59,965
I'll buy you a drink.

1040
01:50:01,925 --> 01:50:03,844
You know...

1041
01:50:03,927 --> 01:50:05,887
a drink?
